The official ball for the 2022 NWFL Premiership Super 6 has been unveiled. The unveiling was done yesterday  by the Chairperson of the NWFL, Aisha Falode, at the Samuel Ogbemudia Stadium, Benin City. The new ball ‘Ivie’ was inspired by the Bini word for Corals. Corals, a beautiful ornament of royalty worn around the neck or adorned on the head by brides and Queens in the Oba’s palace for grand occasions or ceremonies. The artwork used for it’s design brings a sense of tradition, which is closely linked with the spirit of the Super 6 tournament.   NFF appoints José Peseiro Super Eagles coach     Vardy scores twice as Leicester beat relegated Watford 5-1     Struijk’s injury-time equaliser against Brighton lifts…   The 2022 NWFL Premiership Super 6 official ball is predominantly white, with a garish upper graphics that combines blue brush stroke prints with striping in neon pink colours. While the logos of the NWFL and Ivie are black. The ‘Ivie’ was comprehensively tested to make sure it is for professional football and was used at the NWFL/Laliga Show Your Other Side Challenge Novelty Match. It has an excellent shape precision, flight stability, predictability after bounce and it is well durable. The 2022 NWFL Premiership Super 6 sponsored by Tulcan Energy Resources will hold at the Samuel Ogbemudia Stadium, Benin, kicking off from the 16th of May to the 22nd of May 2022. The champion will go home with a cash prize N5million, first runners up N3million and third place N2million.